{"word":"G3709 - ὀργή - orgḗ - or-gay' - Anger","slug":"G3709","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ὀργή</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>orgḗ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>or-gay'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Anger"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03BF;&#x0313;&#x03C1;&#x03B3;&#x03B7;&#x0301; - orge&#x0304;</b> - <i>or-gay'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G3713\">G3713</a>; properly <i>desire</i> (as a <i>reaching</i> forth or <i>excitement</i> of the mind), that is, (by analogy) violent <i>passion</i> (<i>ire</i>, or [justifiable] <i>abhorrence</i>); by implication <i>punishment:</i> - anger, indignation, vengeance, wrath."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G3710\">G3710</a>, <a href=\"#/G3711\">G3711</a>, <a href=\"#/G3949\">G3949</a>, <a href=\"#/G3950\">G3950</a>"}]}